/*E*/
/*S*/ Einleitung
@NODE "Einleitung" "LockFreshPens-Documentation / Introduction"
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}@{bpen 4} 1. Introduction @{bpen 0}@{ub}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}LockFreshPens is a program which is for setting the FreshPalette at
boottime and guarants that the colors can be used but not changed by other
programs. This program is copied during the installation of FreshIcons into
your C: Drawer.

@{par}If all needed colors could be set this way, a socalled ENV-Variable
PALETTESET containing the value FRESH is created. This ENV-Variable shows
other programs, that the FreshPalette is active. So the other programs can
build their GUIs using the FreshPalette.

@{par}To guarantee that the FreshPalette is still active after you changed
the screenmode of the Workbench on your command the library-function
OpenWorkbench is changed (patched), so that after opening the Workbench-screen
the needed colors will be reserved and set directly.

@{par}LockFreshPens should be called in the user-startup. You should take care
for iprefs (or fastiprefs) is executed prior to the execution of the user-startup.
Otherwise it can happen that the Workbench-screen gets opened (and closed) more than once while booting.

@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Bedienung
@NODE "Bedienung" "LockFreshPens-Documentation / Usage"
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}@{bpen 4} 2. Usage @{bpen 0}@{ub}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}LockFreshPens absolutely should be started in your user-startup.
Normally the FreshIcons-Installerscript does this entry for you. Therefor
you should agree this entry in the user-startup during the installation.

@{par}After the start LockFreshPens runs in the background but needs no
processortime at all (it only need 20KBytes of memory). So it's wise to
start LockFreshPens with the run command. Otherwise the shell you run it
from is blocked. For the user-startup it would lead to locking the system
while booting. You can break LockFreshPens with CTRL-C.

@{par}To find out which options LockFreshPens understands, run it in a shell with a "?" as parameter:
@{par}@{apen 10}LockFreshPens ?@{apen 1}

@{par}Now LockFreshPens prints the following:
@{par}@{apen 10}QUIET/S,FORCE/S,PATCH/S,FULL/S,MAGIC8/S:@{apen 1}

The "@{apen 14}/S@{apen 1}" MUST NOT be give, 'cause it just means that this parameter is a switch.

@{par}The first option is @{apen 13}QUIET@{apen 1}. If it is given then LockFreshPens does no output.

@{par}@{apen 9}Advantage:@{apen 1} When running in the user-startup, no bothering window will be opened.
@{par}@{apen 9}Disadvantage:@{apen 1} If started from Shell you won't be informed about success or failure of LockFreshPens.

@{par}The second option @{apen 13}FORCE@{apen 1} lets LockFreshPens set the colors even if LockFreshPens is already running.
It is also tried to reserve the colors again. This option is usefule, if an other program
has set the colors instead of ther locked state and you want back your fantastic colors.

@{par}The option @{apen 13}PATCH@{apen 1} is used if you want to have right
colors even after your Workbenchs'-screenmode was changed or a program
closed the Workbench for a time. Only if this option is given, the
OpenWorkbench-function of the intuition.library will be patched. This is
necessary because the later reserving of the colors than direct after
openning the screen will almost never succeed, because the WBPattern
program of the AmigaOS also tries to lock some colors for its patterns.
To solve this problem this way of patching is gone.

@{par}The fourth option of LockFreshPens @{apen 13}FULL@{apen 1} needs to be explained exactly.
@{par}With the palette-preferences-program of the AmigaOS (in the
Prefs-Drawer) you can set only 8 colors (as far as existing) of the
Workbench-screen. These are the first and the last 4 colors. But the
palette of the FreshIcons consists of 16 colors. When LockFreshPens is
started the first and the last 4 colors are already reserved by the system.
LockFreshPens now has the possibility, but not the right to set these
colornumbers. If you specify the FULL option the colors are set inspite of
that. Often this option will be used in conjunction with the FORCE option.

@{par}@{apen 13}MAGIC8@{apen 1} solves problems on 8-Color Workbenches. If you
work with an 8-color WB one day, you will predictate that the icons may look green.
This is because the last colors are set by the Palette-preferences program
of the AmigaOS. On an 16-color WB these green colors are right but not with 8-Colors.
To fix this, with this option sets the right colors on WB with 8-colors.
This is not system-conform but you don't need to specify this option (and it doesn't hurt).

@{par}The colorvalues used by LockFreshPens can be set in a config-file in your s: drawer.
Sure, it isn't very useful, but some guys want to have this color a bit lighter and this
color a bit darker and so on...

@{par}You use LockFreshPens on your own risk. I will take no responsibility.
But it was testet very hard and i use it too.

@ENDNODE
